text: 's-Gravendeel is a former municipality in the Dutch province of South Holland. In 2007, 9,023 people lived there. Since 2007, it had been part to Binnenmaas. Since 2019, it has been part of the new municipality of Hoeksche Waard.Wet samenvoeging gemeenten Binnenmaas, Cromstrijen, Korendijk, Oud-Beijerland en Strijen, 11 July 2018, accessed at overheid.nl == References == Category:21st- century disestablishments in the Netherlands Category:Settlements in South Holland Category:Former municipalities of South Holland Category:Hoeksche Waard
